                  |\n535-| `UserPromptSubmit`   | Yes        | Blocks prompt processing and erases the prompt                                |\n536-| `Stop`               | Yes        | Prevents Claude from stopping, continues the conversation                     |\n537:| `SubagentStop`       | Yes        | Prevents the subagent from stopping                                           |\n538-| `TeammateIdle`       | Yes        | Prevents the teammate from going idle (teammate continues working)            |\n539-| `TaskCreated`        | Yes        | Prevents the task from being created                                          |\n540-| `TaskCompleted`      | Yes        | Prevents the task from being marked as completed                              |\n--\n606-\n607-| Events                                                                                                                      | Decision pattern               | Key fields                                                                                                                                                          |\n608-| :-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :----------------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n609:| UserPromptSubmit, PostToolUse, PostToolUseFailure, Stop, SubagentStop, ConfigChange                                         | Top-level `decision`           | `decision: \"block\"`, `reason`                                                                                                                                       |\n610-| TeammateIdle, TaskCreated, TaskCompleted                                                                                    | Exit code or `continue: false` | Exit code 2 blocks the action with stderr feedback. JSON `{\"continue\": false, \"stopReason\": \"...\"}` also stops the teammate entirely, matching `Stop` hook behavior |\n611-| PreToolUse                                                                                                                  | `hookSpecificOutput`           | `permissionDecision` (allow/deny/ask), `permissionDecisionReason`                                                                                                   |\n612-| PermissionRequest                                                                                                           | `hookSpecificOutput`           | `decision.behavior` (allow/deny)                                                                                                                                    |\n--\n619-\n620-<Tabs>\n621-  <Tab title=\"Top-level decision\">\n622:    Used by `UserPromptSubmit`, `PostToolUse`, `PostToolUseFailure`, `Stop`, `SubagentStop`, and `ConfigChange`. The only value is `\"block\"`. To allow the action to proceed, omit `decision` from your JSON, or exit 0 without any JSON at all:\n623-\n624-    ```json  theme={null}\n625-    {\n--\n1272-}\n1273-```\n1274-\n1275:### SubagentStop\n1276-\n1277-Runs when a Claude Code subagent has finished responding. Matches on agent type, same values as SubagentStart.\n1278-\n1279:#### SubagentStop input\n1280-\n1281:[Omitted long matching line]\n1282-\n1283-```json theme={null}\n1284-{\n--\n1286-  \"transcript_path\": \"~/.claude/projects/.../abc123.jsonl\",\n1287-  \"cwd\": \"/Users/...\",\n1288-  \"permission_mode\": \"default\",\n1289:  \"hook_event_name\": \"SubagentStop\",\n1290-  \"stop_hook_active\": false,\n1291-  \"agent_id\": \"def456\",\n1292-  \"agent_type\": \"Explore\",\n1293-  \"agent_transcript_path\": \"~/.claude/projects/.../abc123/subagents/agent-def456.jsonl\",\n1294:  \"last_assistant_message\": \"Analysis complete. Found 3 potential issues...\"\n1295-}\n1296-```\n1297-\n1298:SubagentStop hooks use the same decision control format as [Stop hooks](#stop-decision-control).\n1299-\n1300-### TaskCreated\n1301-\n--\n1416-\n1417-#### Stop input\n1418-\n1419:In addition to the [common input fields](#common-input-fields), Stop hooks receive `stop_hook_active` and `last_assistant_message`. The `stop_hook_active` field is `true` when Claude Code is already continuing as a result of a stop hook. Check this value or process the transcript to prevent Claude Code from running indefinitely. The `last_assistant_message` field contains the text content of Claude's final response, so hooks can access it without parsing the transcript file.\n1420-\n1421-```json theme={null}\n1422-{\n--\n1426-  \"permission_mode\": \"default\",\n1427-  \"hook_event_name\": \"Stop\",\n1428-  \"stop_hook_active\": true,\n1429:  \"last_assistant_message\": \"I've completed the refactoring. Here's a summary...\"\n1430-}\n1431-```\n1432-\n1433-#### Stop decision control\n1434-\n1435:`Stop` and `SubagentStop` hooks can control whether Claude continues. In addition to the [JSON output fields](#json-output) available to all hooks, your hook script can return these event-specific fields:\n1436-\n1437-| Field      | Description                                                                |\n1438-| :--------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n--\n1452-\n1453-#### StopFailure input\n1454-\n1455:In addition to the [common input fields](#common-input-fields), StopFailure hooks receive `error`, optional `error_details`, and optional `last_assistant_message`. The `error` field identifies the error type and is used for matcher filtering.\n1456-\n1457-| Field                    | Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |\n1458-| :----------------------- | :----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n1459-| `error`                  | Error type: `rate_limit`, `authentication_failed`, `billing_error`, `invalid_request`, `server_error`, `max_output_tokens`, or `unknown`                                                                                                         |\n1460-| `error_details`          | Additional details about the error, when available                                                                                                                                                                                               |\n1461:| `last_assistant_message` | The rendered error text shown in the conversation. Unlike `Stop` and `SubagentStop`, where this field holds Claude's conversational output, for `StopFailure` it contains the API error string itself, such as `\"API Error: Rate limit reached\"` |\n1462-\n1463-```json theme={null}\n1464-{\n--\n1468-  \"hook_event_name\": \"StopFailure\",\n1469-  \"error\": \"rate_limit\",\n1470-  \"error_details\": \"429 Too Many Requests\",\n1471:  \"last_assistant_message\": \"API Error: Rate limit reached\"\n1472-}\n1473-```\n1474-\n--\n1968-- `PostToolUseFailure`\n1969-- `PreToolUse`\n1970-- `Stop`\n1971:- `SubagentStop`\n1972-- `TaskCompleted`\n1973-- `TaskCreated`\n1974-- `UserPromptSubmit`\n--\n2049-\n2050-### Example: Multi-criteria Stop hook\n2051-\n2052:This `Stop` hook uses a detailed prompt to check three conditions before allowing Claude to stop. If `\"ok\"` is `false`, Claude continues working with the provided reason as its next instruction. `SubagentStop` hooks use the same format to evaluate whether a [subagent](/en/sub-agents) should stop:\n2053-\n2054-```json theme={null}\n2055-{",
