with current versions. The team is running relatively recent versions (Feb-Apr 2026 timeframe).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing ML Code Implementation\n\n**Status**: Prototype/skeleton code exists but **no NBA data integration**\n\n**Files Present**:\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/model/prototype_train.py` (Complete)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py` (14 tests, all passing)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/model/__init__.py` (Empty)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/tests/__init__.py` (Empty)\n\n**Prototype Implementation Details**:\n- XGBoost binary classifier with configurable hyperparameters (n_estimators=300, max_depth=4)\n- Three feature combinations (A: 6 features, B: 9 features, C: 13 features)\n- TimeSeriesSplit cross-validation (n_splits=5, gap=1) for temporal data\n- SHAP-based feature importance analysis\n- Synthetic data generation for testing (no real NBA data)\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Addresses temporal leakage with `.shift(1)` before rolling window operations\n- Uses both SHAP (primary) and built-in XGBoost importance methods\n- Tests verified to prevent data leakage\n\n---\n\n### 4. Missing Data Integration Components\n\n**Not Yet Implemented** (Required for TS-001 story):\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/data/nba_client.py` (NBA API wrapper)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/data/fetch_team_stats.py` (Team stats fetching)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/data/storage.py` (Parquet storage layer)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/data/__init__.py`\n\nThe pipeline currently uses **synthetic data only** for testing.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Source Configuration\n\n**Primary Data Source**: NBA Stats API via `nba_api` library (version 1.11.4)\n\n**Configuration**:\n- No `.env` files found (no credentials stored in repo)\n- Planned endpoints (from CODEBASE.md):\n  - `LeagueGameLog` - Season game logs and box scores\n  - `BoxScoreFourFactorsV2` - Pre-computed eFG%, TOV%, OREB%, FTR\n  - `BoxScoreAdvancedV2` - Advanced