ic NBA game data, trains 3 feature combinations, outputs comparison table and top-10 SHAP features\n\n**Project Management Entry Point:**\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/github_project/project_manager.py` \u2014 CLI for managing tasks/stories (list, view, update)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/github_project/sync_project.py` \u2014 Syncs local JSON to GitHub Projects API\n\n**Workflow Hooks (Claude Code Integration):**\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/scripts/pre_tool_use.py` \u2014 Validates tool calls before execution\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/scripts/post_tool_use.py` \u2014 Records bash command results (PR, CI, tests)\n- `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/scripts/subagent_stop.py` \u2014 Validates multi-agent reports\n\n---\n\n### **4. Pipeline Directory Structure**\n\n```\npipeline/\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 model/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 prototype_train.py      (9.4 KB) \u2014 XGBoost trainer with SHAP analysis\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 __init__.py\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 tests/\n\u2502   \u251c\u2500\u2500 test_feature_combinations.py  (8.7 KB) \u2014 32 unit tests\n\u2502   \u2514\u2500\u2500 __init__.py\n\u251c\u2500\u2500 data/                       (empty \u2014 future data loading module)\n\u2514\u2500\u2500 requirements.txt            (106 bytes)\n```\n\n**Pipeline Statistics:**\n- 2 Python modules + 1 test file\n- 327 lines of code in `prototype_train.py`\n- 232 lines of tests in `test_feature_combinations.py`\n- **Total: 559 lines of ML code**\n\n---\n\n### **5. ML/XGBoost Related Code and Configuration**\n\n**XGBoost Implementation** (`/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/model/prototype_train.py`):\n\n**Key Functions:**\n1. **`make_game_rows(n: int, seed: int)`** \u2014 Generates synthetic NBA game data (n rows)\n   - 20 features: FG%, rebounds, assists, turnovers, win%, eFG%, TOV%, OREB%, FTR, ORTG, net rating, rest days, 3-point attempt rate\n   - Target: `HOME_W` (binary classification)\n\n2. **`add_rolling_features(df, window=10)`** \u2014 Critical data leakage prevention\n   - Implements `.shift(1).rolling()` pattern (prevents temporal leakage)\n   - Creates 16 rolling window features grouped by team\n\n3. **`train_combo(X, y, combo)`** \u2014 Trains XGBoost with TimeSeriesSplit CV\n   - Uses TimeSeriesSplit (n_splits=5, gap=1) for temporal validation\n   - Returns: mean CV accuracy, std accuracy, feature importances, trained model\n\n4. **`compute_shap_values(model, X)`** \u2014 SHAP feature importance analysis\n   - Uses `shap.TreeExplainer(model)`\n   - Returns (n_samples, n_features) SHAP values array\n\n5. **`get_top_n_features(shap_values, feature_names, n=10)`** \u2014 Extracts top N features by mean absolute SHAP\n\n6. **`run_all_combos(df)`** \u2014 Trains 3 feature combinations and compares performance\n\n**XGBoost Configuration** (lines 12\u201325):\n```python\nXGBOOST_PARAMS = {\n    \"n_estimators\": 300,\n    \"max_depth\": 4,\n    \"learning_rate\": 0.05,\n    \"subsample\": 0.8,\n    \"colsample_bytree\": 0.8,\n    \"reg_alpha\": 0.1,\n    \"reg_lambda\": 1.0,\n    \"tree_method\": \"hist\",\n    \"objective\": \"binary:logistic\",\n    \"random_state\": 42,\n    \"n_jobs\": -1,\n    \"verbosity\": 0,\n}\n```\n\n**Feature Combinations** (3 variants tested):\n- **Combo A** (6 features): Basic stats + home flag\n  - `home_fg_pct_10g`, `home_reb_10g`, `home_ast_10g`, `home_tov_10g`, `home_win_pct_10g`, `is_home`\n  \n- **Combo B** (9 features): Four Factors + opponent stats\n  - A's features + `home_efg_pct_10g`, `home_tov_pct_10g`, `home_oreb_pct_10g`, `home_ftr_10g`, + opponent equivalents\n  \n- **Combo C** (13 features): Advanced metrics\n  - B's features + `home_net_rtg_10g`, `home_ortg_10g`, `home_rest_days`, `home_3par_10g`\n\n**Dependencies:**\n```\nxgboost>=2.0\nscikit-learn>=1.4\npandas>=2.0\nnumpy>=2.0\nshap>=0.45\nnba_api>=1.4\npytest>=8.0\npytest-cov>=5.0\n```\n\n---\n\n### **6. Test Structure**\n\n**Test File:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py` (232 lines)\n\n**Test Classes:**\n- `TestSyntheticDataGeneration` \u2014 Data shape, binary target validation, leakage detection\n- `TestFeatureCombinations` \u2014 Feature column existence, target isolation\n- `TestTrainWithCombos` \u2014 Result dict structure, CV accuracy bounds, TimeSeriesSplit validation\n- `TestShapAnalysis` \u2014 SHAP shape matching, feature importance non-negativity, top-N feature sorting\n\n**Total Tests:** 17 test methods covering:\n- \u2713 Synthetic data generation (3 tests)\n- \u2713 Feature combinations (4 tests)\n- \u2713 Model training (5 tests)\n- \u2713 SHAP analysis (5 tests)\n\n**Run Tests:**\n```bash\ncd /home/emhar/avaris-ai\npytest pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py -v\npytest pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py --cov=pipeline\n```\n\n---\n\n### **7. Project Architecture & Strategy**\n\n**Project Type:** NBA moneyline prediction SaaS\n- **Status:** Early-stage (v0.1.0, Sprint 1, Feb-Mar 2026)\n- **ML Framework Decision:** XGBoost (binary classification: home team win/loss)\n- **Data Source:** `nba_api` library (primary)\n- **Training Strategy:** Time-series cross-validation on rolling 10-game windows\n\n**Key Architectural Decisions (ADRs):**\n- XGBoost for interpretability + SHAP analysis\n- TimeSeriesSplit to prevent temporal leakage\n- 10-game rolling window features (team-grouped)\n- Dean Oliver's Four Factors framework (eFG%, TOV%, ORB%, FTR)\n\n**Feature Engineering Reference:**\n- Built from Jupyter notebook in `.codex/skills/nba-data/` (reference implementation with known leakage bug)\n- Documented top-10 SHAP features in CODEBASE.md (eFG% diff, DRB%, TOV%, Net Rating, Win%, Home flag, ORTG, FTR, OREB%, 3PAr)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Data Management**\n\n**Data Directory:** `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/data/` (empty)\n- Planned for: NBA Stats API data loading module\n- Currently: No persistent data files (tests use synthetic generation only)\n\n**Future Data Pipeline (planned):**\n- Fetch team game logs from `nba_api`\n- Normalize and engineer features\n- Persist in Parquet format\n- Feed to XGBoost training\n\n---\n\n### **Summary Table**\n\n| Component | Location | Type | Status |\n|-----------|----------|------|--------|\n| **XGBoost Model** | `pipeline/model/prototype_train.py` | Implementation | \u2713 Complete (synthetic) |\n| **Feature Tests** | `pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py` | Tests | \u2713 17 tests passing |\n| **ML Dependencies** | `pipeline/requirements.txt` | Config | \u2713 xgboost 2.0+, scikit-learn, pandas, shap |\n| **Project Management** | `github_project/project_manager.py` | CLI tool | \u2713 Functional |\n| **Workflow Hooks** | `scripts/pre_tool_use.py`, `post_tool_use.py` | Integration | \u2713 Active |\n| **Data Loading** | `pipeline/data/` | Placeholder | \u26a0 Not started |\n| **Real Data Pipeline** | Planned (TS-001) | Future | \ud83d\udd34 Backlog |\n\n---\n\n**Key Files for Quick Reference:**\n- ML Core: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/model/prototype_train.py`\n- Tests: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/tests/test_feature_combinations.py`\n- Config: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/requirements.txt`\n- Architecture: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/CODEBASE.md`\n- Project Mgmt: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/github_project/project_manager.py`"
