laceholders & Incomplete Work\n\n**Completed (SK-001 Research Spike)**:\n- \u2705 Feature importance ranking documented (top 10 features in CODEBASE.md)\n- \u2705 Feature set recommendations (3 combinations with pros/cons)\n- \u2705 Prototype training script with 3 feature combinations\n- \u2705 Test suite for feature leakage detection\n- \u2705 SHAP-based importance analysis\n\n**Not Yet Implemented (Blocking Tasks for TS-001)**:\n1. **Data Ingestion** (T-010, T-011, T-012)\n   - NBA API client with rate limiting\n   - Team stats fetcher (box scores, advanced metrics)\n   - Parquet storage with season partitioning\n\n2. **Feature Engineering** (T-013)\n   - Rolling window aggregations (proper .shift(1).rolling() pattern)\n   - Four Factors calculation (eFG%, TOV%, OREB%, FTR)\n   - Rest days context ingestion from schedule\n\n3. **Training Pipeline** (T-014)\n   - Orchestration: load raw data \u2192 engineer features \u2192 train models \u2192 store artifacts\n   - Hyperparameter tuning framework\n\n4. **Prediction Generation** (T-015)\n   - Daily prediction script for upcoming games\n   - Confidence/probability outputs\n\n5. **Firestore Publishing** (T-016)\n   - Write predictions to Firebase for frontend consumption\n\n6. **Frontend** (Not in pipeline/)\n   - Next.js site (TS-012) \u2014 not yet created\n\n---\n\n### 5. Feature Engineering & XGBoost Documentation\n\n**Top 10 Features by SHAP Importance** (Cross-Study Rankings in CODEBASE.md):\n1. eFG% differential (10g rolling) \u2014 Four Factors, top SHAP\n2. DRB% (10g rolling) \u2014 Possession control\n3. TOV% (10g rolling) \u2014 Turnover efficiency\n4. Net Rating (10g rolling) \u2014 Advanced metric combining ORTG+DRTG\n5. Win % (10g rolling) \u2014 Pre-game predictor\n6. Home/Away flag \u2014 Simple but consistent\n7. ORTG differential (10g rolling) \u2014 Scoring efficiency\n8. FTR (10g rolling) \u2014 Four Factors aggression\n9. OREB% (10g rolling) \u2014 Second-chance points\n10. 3PAr (10g rolling) \u2014 Offensive style indicator\n\n**XGBoost Accuracy Benchmarks** (from Literature):\n- Basic stats only: 63-67%\n- Four Factors: 67-70%\n- Extended (Combo C): 70-74%\n- **Production Target**: AUC > 0.72\n\n**Key Feature Engineering Best Practices** (Documented):\n- Rolling windows: Always `.shift(1).rolling()` to prevent leakage\n- Cross-validation: `TimeSeriesSplit(n_splits=5, gap=1)` (never K-fold)\n- Feature importance: SHAP TreeExplainer (primary), built-in gain (secondary)\n- Temporal safety: Sort by GAME_DATE before any split\n\n---\n\n### 6. Architectural Decisions\n\n**File**: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/.claude/worktrees/SPRINT-001/SK-002/project2/docs/architecture/decisions.md`\n\n**Key Decisions Relevant to Pipeline**:\n\n| Decision | Choice | Rationale |\n|----------|--------|-----------|\n| DECISION-002 | XGBoost (Python) | Gold standard for tabular data, fast nightly retraining, strong Python ecosystem |\n| DECISION-007 | nba_api library | Most popular wrapper for stats.nba.com, free, active maintenance |\n| DECISION-008 | Feature Combo C | 13 features (Four Factors + advanced + context) expected 70-74% accuracy |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Dependencies State\n\n**File**: `/home/emhar/avaris-ai/pipeline/requirements.txt`\n\n```\nxgboost>=2.0\nscikit-learn>=1.4\npandas>=2.0\nnumpy>=2.0\nshap>=0.45\nnba_api>=1.4\npytest>=8.0\npytest-cov>=5.0\n```\n\n**Currently Installed** (in venv):\n- \u2705 All required packages ready\n- \u2705 nba_api 1.11.4 (for future data fetching)\n- \u2705 pandas 3.0.2 (data manipulation)\n- \u2705 pytest 9.0.2 (testing framework)\n- \u2705 pyarrow 22.0.0 (Parquet support)\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table\n\n| Category | Status | Details |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| **Model Code (prototype_train.py)** | \u2705 COMPLETE | 326 LOC, 3 feature combos, SHAP analysis, CLI-ready |\n| **Test Suite** | \u2705 COMPLETE | 16 tests (54% coverage), all passing, leakage detection |\n| **Data Ingestion** | \u274c MISSING | T-010/T-011/T-012: No NBA API client, fetch, or storage code |\n| **Feature Engineering** | \u274c MISSING | T-013: No feature pipeline beyond prototype |\n| **Training Orchestration** | \u274c MISSING | T-014: No pipeline runner or hyperparameter tuning |\n| **Prediction Generation** | \u274c MISSING | T-015: No daily prediction script |\n| **Firestore Publishing** | \u274c MISSING | T-016: No backend publication layer |\n| **Documentation** | \u2705 COMPLETE | CODEBASE.md (top features, benchmarks), decisions.md (architecture) |\n| **Dependencies** | \u2705 READY | All packages installed, pinned versions defined |\n\n---\n\n## Test Coverage Summary\n\n```\nCoverage: 54% (110 statements, 51 missed)\nAll 16 tests: PASSING \u2705\nTest execution time: 6.32s\nCoverage focus: Data generation and feature validation\nGap: CLI/main() functions not unit-tested\n```\n\n---\n\n## Blockers for Next Phase (TS-001)\n\nThe prototype is **research-complete** for SK-001. To implement TS-001 (NBA Stats API data ingestion), you need:\n\n1. **Implement `pipeline/data/nba_client.py`** (T-010)\n   - Wrapper around nba_api with rate limiting and retry logic\n   - Must handle custom HTTP headers for stats.nba.com\n   \n2. **Implement `pipeline/data/fetch_team_stats.py`** (T-011)\n   - Fetch LeagueGameLog + BoxScoreFourFactorsV2 + BoxScoreAdvancedV2\n   - Aggregate by team and season\n\n3. **Implement `pipeline/data/storage.py`** (T-012)\n   - Parquet writing with snappy compression\n   - Season-based partitioning\n\nOnce data ingestion exists, feature engineering pipeline (T-013) can use real NBA data instead of synthetic data. **Note**: TDD=False planned for TS-001 per CODEBASE.md \u2014 implement directly with validation via running the code."
