            "I've found several relevant sources on NBA game prediction using XGBoost and binary classifiers. Here's a summary of the key benchmarks and findings:\n\n## XGBoost Performance in NBA Game Prediction\n\nXGBoost demonstrated superiority in comparative experiments comparing multiple machine learning algorithms using metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, F1 Score, and AUC value in ten-fold cross-validation. More specifically, the XGBoost algorithm consistently showed the best performance regarding accuracy and precision metrics.\n\n## Specific Accuracy Benchmarks\n\nSeveral studies report varying accuracy levels for NBA game prediction:\n\n- One model achieved nearly 80% accuracy\n- A composite stacked model reached 76.8% accuracy on predicting 2018 NBA playoffs, with extraordinary accuracy of 85.7% for Eastern Conference Finals and 100% for Conference Finals\n- A study comparing multiple ML models achieved 65.50% prediction accuracy for the NBA\n- One XGBoost implementation reported an AUC of 0.8041708 with MSE of 0.1803835\n\n## Comparative Studies\n\nIn terms of AUC and F1 Score metrics, XGBoost performed excellently, consistently ranking in the top 2 across ten-fold cross-validation comparative experiments for different time periods.\n\nThe accuracy benchmarks vary considerably depending on the features used, dataset scope, and prediction context (regular season vs. playoffs), with XGBoost consistently showing strong performance across these studies."
